modules.description: This module provides functions to open and query a binary IP geolocation database, retrieving detailed proxy and network information for specific IP addresses. It works with metadata structures containing file handles and database indices, along with record types that represent IP lookup results, including country, region, ISP, and threat data. Concrete use cases include IP-based access control, fraud detection, and geolocation analytics.

This module enables IP address analysis by querying a binary geolocation database, returning detailed proxy and network metadata. It operates on IP addresses and database indices to retrieve structured records with location, ISP, and threat information. Developers can implement access control, fraud detection, or analytics based on IP geolocation data. For example, given an IP, it can return the country, region, and whether the IP is associated with a known threat.
